casebody.data:
STATE of Louisiana
v.
Kenneth MOORE No. 2018-KK-1051 Supreme Court of Louisiana. June 23, 2018 ON SUPERVISORY WRITS TO THE CRIMINAL DISTRICT COURT, PARISH OF ORLEANS Stay denied. Writ denied. CRICHTON, J., additionally concurs and assigns reasons. I additionally concur in the denial of the State's writ application because the trial court has not made a final judgment on the motion in limine that is the subject thereof, thus rendering the application premature.
